HEADWORD: Encompassment
<hw>En*com"pass*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
surrounding, or the state of being surrounded; circumvention.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By this <qex>encompassment</qex> and drift of question.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

